full_text: 7. Know when to shut it off. Yes, this the hardest for me, but you must to counter #1 when the day ends & know when to pick up your life again. It'll help your family and yourself respect the boundaries knowing that when you're off, you are someone they can count out.
full_text(utf-8): b"7. Know when to shut it off. Yes, this the hardest for me, but you must to counter #1 when the day ends & know when to pick up your life again. It'll help your family and yourself respect the boundaries knowing that when you're off, you are someone they can count out."

full_text: 6. Have back up work spaces (plural) you can count on each and every time. Okay, this one might be impossible right now, but I have 4... yes, 4! ... coffee shops w/in biking distance. There will be times you'll need to for a change of pace or wifi issues. Have the b/u plan.
full_text(utf-8): b"6. Have back up work spaces (plural) you can count on each and every time. Okay, this one might be impossible right now, but I have 4... yes, 4! ... coffee shops w/in biking distance. There will be times you'll need to for a change of pace or wifi issues. Have the b/u plan."

full_text: 5. Get up and walk. No I mean it. Take at least 1 walk for 15-30 mins a day. I've had some of my best ideas, thoughts and solutions while cruising the strand after running the work meeting gauntlet. At the very least you'll get some fresh air and fresh perspective.
full_text(utf-8): b"5. Get up and walk. No I mean it. Take at least 1 walk for 15-30 mins a day. I've had some of my best ideas, thoughts and solutions while cruising the strand after running the work meeting gauntlet. At the very least you'll get some fresh air and fresh perspective."

full_text: 4. Make one call a day to a co-worker, any co-worker, for any reason. It's important to have that human connection outside of a chat room or email. You'll also quickly get caught up on the internal workings, meetings and pivots in five-minutes or less.
full_text(utf-8): b"4. Make one call a day to a co-worker, any co-worker, for any reason. It's important to have that human connection outside of a chat room or email. You'll also quickly get caught up on the internal workings, meetings and pivots in five-minutes or less."

full_text: 3. Turn off the TV. Don't even tempt yourself. I work in sports and I won't even keep it on our CBS HQ product since it can easily become a distraction.
full_text(utf-8): b"3. Turn off the TV. Don't even tempt yourself. I work in sports and I won't even keep it on our CBS HQ product since it can easily become a distraction."

full_text: 2. Have a routine. Yes, that includes having a drop dead time to take a shower, change and eat built into your morning.
